# Debugger — backend

Specialist context for debugging the FastAPI + PostgreSQL + SSE layer.

## Investigation sequence

1. Get the exact HTTP status, error body, and stack trace
2. Identify layer: Auth middleware → Route handler → Repository → DB / chain proxy
3. Check asyncpg connection pool exhaustion if DB errors
4. For SSE failures: check the `StreamingResponse` generator and chain invocation
5. For auth failures: check JWT expiry, algorithm, and token revocation (issue #5)

## Key files

| Layer | File |
|-------|------|
| Routes | `app/src/app/routers/` |
| Auth | `app/src/app/auth/jwt.py`, `app/src/app/auth/dependencies.py` |
| DB pool | `app/src/app/database.py` |
| Repositories | `app/src/app/repositories/` |
| SSE proxy | `app/src/app/routers/chat.py` |
| Config | `app/src/app/config.py` |

## Common failure patterns

| Symptom | Likely cause |
|---------|-------------|
| 500 on all requests | asyncpg pool not initialized — check `app.state.db_pool` |
| 401 on valid token | JWT secret mismatch or expired `APP_SECRET_KEY` |
| SSE stream drops | `chain/` pipeline exception not caught — check `chat.py` error handling |
| Slow response | IMDb retry delay (issue #8) — check LangSmith trace for `enrich_imdb` node |

## Anti-Focus

Do NOT fix the code. Produce a defect report and hand off to Developer persona.
